Times LIVE picked up the video on Facebook after motorist Murray Kernick posted it on Saturday.On Monday morning the video was viewed 175 000 times and had been shared 4 000 times.But by Tuesday morning the video was watched 828 000 times and was shared by 18 000 people. It has gone viral for all the right reasons a normal day in traffic changed in an instant to a moment to remember. In case you missed it here is the video again: Directing traffic South African style! Classic :) Posted by Murray Kernick on Saturday, March 11, 2017Directing traffic South African style! Classic :)